content:
Correctness_Score: 1.0
Style_Score: 0.8
Simplicity_Score: 0.9
Robustness_Score: 0.8
Reasoning: Correctness was validated by implementing a brute-force solver that tracks used medicines and comparing it to the provided solution; I ran exhaustive checks for small grids (H,W ≤ 3) with many obstacle/medicine placements and several hundred random cases and found no mismatches, so the implementation appears functionally correct. Style is concise with clear variable names and brief comments (BFS and pruning are explained), but it lacks a module docstring and some explanatory comments for the pruning logic, so I give 0.8. Simplicity is high because the solution uses an efficient BFS with per-cell best-energy pruning and minimal extra logic (one minor unused variable), so 0.9. Robustness is good: the code handles the problem constraints and tested edge cases, but has small maintainability issues (no explicit S/T validation, unused variable) so I score 0.8.
